      "content": "Substantive due process acts as a vital shield against the \"tyranny of the majority\" by granting courts the power to strike down laws that violate fundamental rights, regardless of whether the majority of voters supports them. This judicial review ensures that minority groups cannot be deprived of essential liberties, such as voting rights or freedom of religion, simply because popular opinion shifts against them. By prioritizing individual constitutional guarantees over transient public opinion, the doctrine maintains a continuous separation between the will of the people and the protection of personal dignity.",
